&lt;h1 id="original-2012-review">Original 2012 review:&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>&amp;hellip; there&amp;rsquo;s really not much to say about this that hasn&amp;rsquo;t been said / won&amp;rsquo;t be said a thousand times over. Long story short, it&amp;rsquo;s a great movie and a hit out of the park for everyone involved. I liked it enough that I&amp;rsquo;m sure to see it again and I strongly suggest that you go to.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>The Cabin in the Woods</title><link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2012/04/18/the-cabin-in-the-woods/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Apr 2012 16:55:52 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2012/04/18/the-cabin-in-the-woods/</guid><description>&lt;p>I generally don&amp;rsquo;t go for horror movies, but the general premise intrigued me. And it doesn&amp;rsquo;t hurt that Joss Whedon co-wrote it. He&amp;rsquo;s had his ups and downs, but in general he&amp;rsquo;s earned at least a second look in my book.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>